TITLE: Netanyahu says he told the US that he opposes a Palestinian state in any postwar scenario
SUMMARY: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu says he has informed the United States that he opposes the establishment of a Palestinian state as part of any postwar scenario

TITLE: An airstrike on southern Syria, likely carried out by Jordan's air force, kills 9
SUMMARY: Syrian opposition activists say an airstrike that was likely carried out by Jordan’s air force on southern Syria has killed at least nine people in the latest of strikes in recent months

TITLE: Spain amends its constitution to replace term ‘handicapped’ with ‘persons with a disability’
SUMMARY: Spain’s Parliament has voted to amend the country's constitution for the third time, removing the term “handicapped” and replacing it with “persons with a disability.”

TITLE: A court of appeals in Thailand hands an activist a 50-year prison term for insulting the monarchy
SUMMARY: A court of appeals in Thailand has handed a political activist what is believed to be a record sentence for the criminal offense of insulting the monarchy

TITLE: Police in Brazil arrest a suspect in the brutal slaying of a Manhattan art dealer
SUMMARY: Brazilian police say that a suspect has been arrested in the brutal killing of an American art dealer who was the co-owner of a prominent gallery in Manhattan

TITLE: Panama Canal traffic cut by more than a third because of drought
SUMMARY: A severe drought that began last year has forced authorities to slash ship crossings by 36% in the Panama Canal, one of the world’s most important trade routes

TITLE: France ramps up weapons production for Ukraine and says Russia is scrutinizing the West's mettle
SUMMARY: France has announced more deliveries of its Caesar artillery system to Ukraine and is accelerating weapons production to avoid depleting its own military stocks while continuing to support the war effort against Russia’s invasion

TITLE: More than 1,000 rally in Russian region in continuing protests over activist's jailing
SUMMARY: More than 1,000 people have rallied in the Russian region of Bashkortostan, continuing a series of protests triggered by the conviction and sentencing of a local activist and handing a new challenge to the Kremlin

TITLE: Russian prosecutors seek lengthy prison terms for suspects in cases linked to the war in Ukraine
SUMMARY: A Russian court in Siberia has sentenced a man to 19 years in prison for shooting a military enlistment officer in an attack last September linked to the war in Ukraine

TITLE: North Korea says it tested a nuclear-capable underwater drone in response to rivals' naval drills
SUMMARY: North Korea says it has tested a nuclear-capable underwater attack drone in response to a combined naval exercise by South Korea, the United States and Japan this week, as it continues to blame its rivals for raising tensions in the region

TITLE: Jordan Henderson apologizes to LGBTQ+ community for his short-lived Saudi move as he arrives at Ajax
SUMMARY: Jordan Henderson has apologized to the LGBTQ+ community that fiercely criticized his transfer from Liverpool to Al-Ettifaq

TITLE: Sami rights activists in Norway charged over protests against wind farm affecting reindeer herding
SUMMARY: A lawyer says some 20 activists have been charged after they blocked several entrances to Norwegian government offices over a wind farm that they say hinders the rights of the Sami Indigenous people to raise reindeer

TITLE: Tata Steel announces plans to cut 2,800 jobs in a blow to Welsh town built on steelmaking
SUMMARY: Indian firm Tata Steel says it will close both blast furnaces at its plant in Port Talbot in Wales, eliminating 2,800 jobs

TITLE: Now eyeing a longer haul, the US reshuffles its warships in the Mediterranean
SUMMARY: The U.S. Navy is reshuffling its warship deployment in the Middle East to maintain dominance in the region

TITLE: British leader Sunak urges Parliament's upper house to swiftly pass Rwanda migration plan
SUMMARY: British Prime Minister Rishi Sunak has laid out a challenge to members of Parliament's unelected upper chamber to swiftly pass his controversial plan to send some asylum-seekers on a one-way trip to Rwanda

TITLE: 15 students and 1 teacher drown when a boat capsizes in a lake in western India
SUMMARY: A fire official in western India says a boat has capsized in a lake and drowned 15 students and one teacher

TITLE: EU Parliament adopts resolution calling for permanent cease-fire in Gaza but Hamas must go
SUMMARY: European lawmakers have adopted a resolution calling for a permanent cease-fire in Israel’s war against Hamas, on the condition that the Palestinian militant group in Gaza be dismantled and that all hostages it holds be released

TITLE: Pakistani airstrikes on Iran killed 4 children and 3 women, a local official tells Iranian state television
SUMMARY: Pakistani airstrikes on Iran killed 4 children and 3 women, a local official tells Iranian state television

TITLE: Mexican soldiers find workshop for making drone bombs, military uniforms
SUMMARY: Mexican soldiers and police say they have found a small factory used to make a kind of bomb usually dropped by drones

TITLE: Health announcements about King Charles III and Kate mark a departure for the tight-lipped UK royals
SUMMARY: The double health announcements from Britain’s royal family have put a spotlight on the private lives of the U.K.‘s senior royals

TITLE: Japan's imperial family hosts a poetry reading with a focus on peace to welcome the new year
SUMMARY: Japanese Empress Masako has expressed her yearning for peace as a mother’s love in her poem, read at an annual celebration of poetry at the Imperial Palace in Tokyo

TITLE: Dominican authorities arrest US rapper Tekashi 6ix9ine on domestic violence charges
SUMMARY: Authorities in the Dominican Republic have arrested U.S. rapper Tekashi 6ix9ine on charges of domestic violence

TITLE: Snubbed by Netanyahu, Red Cross toes fine line trying to help civilians in Israel-Hamas conflict
SUMMARY: The International Committee of the Red Cross has been losing influence, funding and staff

TITLE: Donkey cart loaded with explosives kills a police officer and critically injures 4 others in Kenya
SUMMARY: Authorities in Kenya say a donkey cart carrying a suspected improvised bomb has blown up at a checkpoint on the Kenya-Somalia border, killing one Kenyan police officer and critically wounding four others

TITLE: Gangs in Haiti have attacked a community for 4 days and residents fear the violence could spread
SUMMARY: Gang members have raided a key community in Haiti’s capital that is home to numerous police officers and has been under siege for four days in an ongoing attack
